Models

Importing custom meshes

Drag and drop blender .fbx files into Assets in Project tab.

Exported 3D files:
- Pro: smaller, more modular design
- Con: slower iterations with export/import
- .FBX, .dae(collada), .3DS, .dexf, .obj

Proprietary formats:
- Pro: quick and simple initially
- Con: bloated with unnecessary data
(do not use for big projects)
- Max, Maya, Blender, Cinema4D, Modo, Lightwave, Cheeta3D and Sketchup

Contents of an FBX
- Meshes
- Animation
- Blend Shapes
- Texture/Materials
- Smoothing group

Blend Shape -> Google image search ex: facial expressions
Smoothing Group -> Create smooth and hard edges


NOTE: Checkout blendwap.com and sketchfab.com

